childElements.name: ApplicationInstructions
childElements.propertySetConfig:
{ "controlWidth" : 12, "label" : "TextBlock1", "text" : "

ARIZONA SUPREME COURT

Legal Document Preparer Business - Initial Registration Instructions

Please read all the following instructions carefully before proceeding. There are several supporting documents listed below which must accompany the online submission. It is recommended that these documents are prepared and assembled prior to beginning the on online application process. To obtain additional assistance, contact the Certification and Licensing Division at LDP@courts.az.gov or visit the Arizona Judicial Department website at https://www.azcourts.gov/cld/Legal-Document-Preparer-Program.

  1. Fees:
    Please refer to ACJA § 7-208(K) to reference the applicable NON-REFUNDABLE fee(s) which are required to submit this application.

  2. Designated Principal:
    Pursuant to Arizona Code of Judicial Administration § 7-208, the designated principal for the business entity MUST be certified as an individual. If the application for designated principal will be submitted simultaneously with the business application, the designated principal must be listed in the “Certified Legal Document Preparers and Trainees” section of the application as a “Pending Application.”.

  3. Business Entity Documentation:
    All Corporations and Limited Liability Companies making application for business entity certification MUST submit, along with the application, a copy of the entity’s Articles of Incorporation/Organization AND a current certificate of Good Standing from the Corporation Commission.

  4. Assumed Name (or D.B.A.):
    While conducting legal document preparer business, a certificate holder shall use the name as shown on the certificate and shall not transact business in this state under an assumed name or under any designation, name or style, corporate or otherwise, other than the real name of the individual unless the individual files with Division staff a license setting forth the name under which business will be transacted.

  5. Background Information:
    If applicant answers “Yes” to any question in the Background Section of this application, the Designated Principal is required to submit a SIGNED statement describing in detail all incidents including (1) names of all parties involved, (2) dates and locations, (3) the names and localities of any courts and/or administrative agencies involved, (4) ) the assigned case or action number, (5) the disposition of each matter, (6) whether the conviction, plea or finding was for a felony, misdemeanor, or open-ended charge, and, (7) any finding of liability.

  6. Certified Legal Document Preparers:
    A list of ALL certified legal document preparers and ALL trainees acting for, or on behalf of, the business entity MUST be submitted with this application. Note: An individual can only qualify as a trainee if they are eligible to obtain individual certification, but for a lack required experience. An individual previously denied certification for any other reason is NOT eligible to act as a trainee. [See Arizona Code of Judicial Administration § 7-208(F)(5)].

  7. Acknowledgment of Designated Principal:
    This form must be signed by the Designated Principal, notarized and uploaded with the application. Please refer to the legal document preparer program link on the Resource Center page of the Certification and Licensing Portal to access the form.

  8. Authorization and Release:
    This form must be signed by the Designated Principal, notarized and uploaded with the application. Please refer to the legal document preparer program link on the Resource Center page of the Certification and Licensing Portal to access the form.

  9. Exemption Agreement and Acknowledgement:
    If a Business Entity Exemption Request is submitted, this form must be signed by the Designated Principal, notarized and uploaded with the application. Please refer to the legal document preparer program link on the Resource Center page of the Certification and Licensing Portal to access the form.

Questions? Call us at (602) 452-3378 or Email us at ldp@courts.az.gov

 
", "show" : null, "dataJSON" : false, "HTMLTemplateId" : "", "textKey" : "", "sanitize" : false }
